"title": "5811: compromise",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5811",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Usually a combination of contrasting values, practices or persons incurring God's disapproval, but it can also be a positive way to achieve a greater good.</p>\n<h2>God forbids compromising associations</h2>\n<h3>Israel was not to associate with paganism</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:3\">EXO 20:3</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:7\">DEU 5:7</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:32-Exod23:33\">EXO 23:32–23:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:12-Exod34:16\">EXO 34:12–34:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:2-Deut7:4\">DEU 7:2–7:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:21\">1KI 18:21</a></p>\n<h3>Christians must not compromise their allegiance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:4\">JAS 4:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:24\">MAT 6:24</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:13\">LUK 16:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:14\">ROM 13:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:14-2Cor6:16\">2CO 6:14–6:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:6-Gal1:9\">GAL 1:6–1:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:8\">JAS 4:8</a></p>\n<h2>Israel's compromises with paganism</h2>\n<h3>In worship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:28-1Kgs12:30\">1KI 12:28–12:30</a></strong> <em>The LORD's action in bringing Israel up out of Egypt is here attributed to the golden calves representing Baal.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:2-Exod32:6\">EXO 32:2–32:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg2:11-Judg2:12\">JDG 2:11–2:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg8:27\">JDG 8:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs1:2-2Kgs1:3\">2KI 1:2–1:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs16:10-2Kgs16:16\">2KI 16:10–16:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:32-2Kgs17:33\">2KI 17:32–17:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:41\">2KI 17:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr28:22\">2CH 28:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:20-Rev2:23\">REV 2:20–2:23</a></p>\n<h3>In foreign alliances</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:1-Isa30:2\">ISA 30:1–30:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr19:2\">2CH 19:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:35-2Chr20:37\">2CH 20:35–20:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr28:16-2Chr28:21\">2CH 28:16–28:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa31:1\">ISA 31:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos5:13\">HOS 5:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos7:8-Hos7:9\">HOS 7:8–7:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos7:11\">HOS 7:11</a></p>\n<h3>In marriage</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:1-1Kgs11:11\">1KI 11:1–11:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs16:31\">1KI 16:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr18:1\">2CH 18:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra9:2\">EZR 9:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:23\">NEH 13:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:25-Neh13:26\">NEH 13:25–13:26</a></p>\n<h2>Motives for compromise</h2>\n<h3>Fear</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:7-Gen26:9\">GEN 26:7–26:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:11-Gen12:13\">GEN 12:11–12:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:18-Gen12:19\">GEN 12:18–12:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:18-Gen19:20\">GEN 19:18–19:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen20:2\">GEN 20:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen20:11\">GEN 20:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:12-Gal2:13\">GAL 2:12–2:13</a></p>\n<h3>Lack of faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen16:1-Gen16:2\">GEN 16:1–16:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:2-Gen15:3\">GEN 15:2–15:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:26-1Kgs12:33\">1KI 12:26–12:33</a></p>\n<h3>Desire for material things</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:21\">JOS 7:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag1:2-Hag1:4\">HAG 1:2–1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:22\">MAT 13:22</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:18-Mark4:19\">MRK 4:18–4:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:14\">LUK 8:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:1-Acts5:4\">ACT 5:1–5:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:10\">2TI 4:10</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of those who refused to compromise</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth3:4\">EST 3:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen39:7-Gen39:12\">GEN 39:7–39:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:13-1Kgs22:14\">1KI 22:13–22:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:18\">DAN 3:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:7-Dan6:10\">DAN 6:7–6:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:2\">2CO 4:2</a></p>\n<h2>Compromise as a mutually acceptable solution</h2>\n<h3>For the sake of the gospel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:19-1Cor9:23\">1CO 9:19–9:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:19-Acts15:20\">ACT 15:19–15:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:28-Acts15:29\">ACT 15:28–15:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:20-Acts21:26\">ACT 21:20–21:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:19-Rom14:22\">ROM 14:19–14:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:1-Rom15:2\">ROM 15:1–15:2</a></p>\n<h3>As an act of wisdom</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:24-1Kgs3:25\">1KI 3:24–3:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:6-1Kgs12:7\">1KI 12:6–12:7</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr10:6-2Chr10:7\">2CH 10:6–10:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer40:9-Jer40:10\">JER 40:9–40:10</a></p>\n<h3>As a means to peace</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen13:8-Gen13:9\">GEN 13:8–13:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:19-Gen26:22\">GEN 26:19–26:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:26-Gen37:27\">GEN 37:26–37:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:8\">PRO 25:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:25\">MAT 5:25</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:58\">LUK 12:58</a></p>",
